<h3><a name="3_3_Adding_OSG_Software_to_Worke"></a> 3.3  Adding OSG Software to Worker Nodes </h3>
<p /> <ul>
<li> Install the worker node (WN) client software on every worker node – pick a method: <ul>
<li> <span class="twikiNewLink">Using RPMs<a href="/bin/edit/Sandbox/InstallWNClient?topicparent=Sandbox.InstallOverview" rel="nofollow" title="Using RPMs (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>
</li> <li> <span class="twikiNewLink">Using a tarball<a href="/bin/edit/Sandbox/InstallWNClientTarball?topicparent=Sandbox.InstallOverview" rel="nofollow" title="Using a tarball (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> – does not require root access or installation into system-wide locations
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> (optional) <span class="twikiNewLink">Install the CernVM-FS client<a href="/bin/edit/Sandbox/InstallCvmfs?topicparent=Sandbox.InstallOverview" rel="nofollow" title="Install the CernVM-FS client (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> to make it easy for user jobs to install needed software from OSG’s OASIS repositories
</li> <li> (optional, advanced) <span class="twikiNewLink">Install gLExec on the OSG worker node<a href="/bin/edit/Sandbox/InstallGlexec?topicparent=Sandbox.InstallOverview" rel="nofollow" title="Install gLExec on the OSG worker node (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>, if you know you need it
</li></ul> 
